quest_title: A fireman of mass 60 kg slides down a pole. He is pressing the pole with a force of 600 N. The coefficient of friction between the hands and the pole is 0.5, with what acceleration will the fireman slide down (g = 10 m/s2)

Net down acceleration

\(= \cfrac { \text { Weight - Friction force } } { \text { Mass } }\)

\(\begin{aligned} & = \cfrac { ( m g - \mu R ) } { m } \\ & = \cfrac { 60 \times 10 - 0.5 \times 600 } { 60 } \\ & = \cfrac { 300 } { 60 } = 5 \mathrm { m } / \mathrm { s } ^ { 2 } \end{aligned}\)

quest_title: The Oxidation of \(\text{SO\(_{2}\)}\) by \(\text{O\(_{2}\)}\) to \(\text{SO\(_{3}\)}\) is an exothermic reaction . the yield of \(\text{SO\(_{3}\)}\) will be maximum if

ans2_txt: Temperature is reduced and pressure is increased
ans3_txt: Both temperature ad pressure are increased
ans4_txt: Both temperature and pressure are decreased
explanation_txt:
We have,

\( 2SO_2 + O_2 \rightleftharpoons 2SO_3 \)

\(\Delta n = 2-3 = -1 < 0 \)

So, forward reaction is favored at high pressure.

As the reaction is exothermic, forward reaction is favored at low temperature.

quest_title: Which of the following would decrease pH of 25 ml of 0.01 M HCl Solution.
explanation_txt:
To decrease pH, concentration of acid should increase.

So, addition of \(0.05M\) acid on \(0.01M\) acid definitely decreases the \(pH\).

Calculations:

For monobacic acid, \([H^+]=N=M\)

Before addition:

\(pH = - \log [M] = 2\)

After addition:

\( M = \cfrac{0.01 \times 25 + 0.05 \times 25}{50} = 0.03 \\ \Rightarrow pH = - \log [M] = 1.52 \)
